// Shopify retirement redirect Worker — store.surprisegranite.com -> www.surprisegranite.com/marketplace
//
// PURPOSE: retire the Shopify storefront and transfer its Google ranking to the
// in-house marketplace. 301s every Shopify product to its marketplace equivalent
// (matched by handle), 410s the crawl-bloat .atom feeds, and sends everything
// else to the marketplace. This is what lets Google collapse the duplicate and
// rank the marketplace pages (the ones that actually sell).
//
// DEPLOY (all in Cloudflare dashboard, ~5 min):
//   1. Workers & Pages -> Create -> paste this file -> Deploy.
//   2. Move store.surprisegranite.com OFF Shopify: in DNS, change the
//      store CNAME (currently -> shops.myshopify.com) to a proxied (orange-cloud)
//      record, then add a Worker Route: store.surprisegranite.com/*  -> this Worker.
//      (While it points at Shopify DNS-only, no Worker/redirect can run — that was the bug.)
//   3. Verify: curl -I https://store.surprisegranite.com/products/<any-handle>
//      should return 301 Location: https://www.surprisegranite.com/marketplace/...
//
// NOTE: this turns the Shopify storefront OFF for that hostname. Make sure the
// marketplace is handling orders before flipping DNS.

const WWW = 'https://www.surprisegranite.com';
const MARKET = WWW + '/marketplace/';
